<div class="bw-wardrobe-page" data-bw-wardrobe-page data-default-variant="{{ wardrobe_variant }}" id="wardrobe-overview">
  <section class="bw-planning-rail">
    <div class="bw-planning-rail__items" aria-label="Wardrobe types">
      <a class="bw-planning-rail__link{% if wardrobe_variant == 'all' %} is-current{% endif %}" href="{{ main_url }}" data-wardrobe-chip="all">All Wardrobes</a>
      <a class="bw-planning-rail__link{% if wardrobe_variant == 'sliding' %} is-current{% endif %}" href="{{ sliding_url }}" data-wardrobe-chip="sliding">Sliding</a>
      <a class="bw-planning-rail__link{% if wardrobe_variant == 'hinged' %} is-current{% endif %}" href="{{ hinged_url }}" data-wardrobe-chip="hinged">Hinged</a>
      <a class="bw-planning-rail__link{% if wardrobe_variant == 'walk-in' %} is-current{% endif %}" href="{{ walk_in_url }}" data-wardrobe-chip="walk-in">Walk-in</a>
      <a class="bw-planning-rail__link bw-planning-rail__link--accent" href="{{ calculator_cta_url }}" data-wardrobe-chip="calculator">Wardrobe Calculator</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bw-wardrobe-block bw-wardrobe-route">
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-head">
      <span class="bw-wardrobe-eyebrow">Route map</span>
      {% if wardrobe_variant == 'sliding' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Sliding wardrobes should move like a guided decision, not a dead-end product page</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">Start with clearance, then settle the panel rhythm, then use the calculator or estimate once the room has a clear sliding brief.</p>
      {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'hinged' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Hinged wardrobes need a better path between room fit, internal structure, and pricing</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">The most useful next step is to compare access, internal storage, and hardware before the project moves into estimate mode.</p>
      {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'walk-in' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Walk-in wardrobes should read like a room strategy, not just a storage layout</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">Use this route map to move from zoning, to planning, to consultation without losing the room-scale context that makes walk-ins work.</p>
      {% else %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Use this page to settle the wardrobe direction before the project moves to pricing</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">The strongest wardrobe briefs start with a clear route: choose the format, understand the room demands, then use the calculator or estimate with intent.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-route-grid">
      {% if wardrobe_variant == 'sliding' %}
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">01</span>
          <h3>Start with clearance</h3>
          <p>Sliding is strongest when it solves a real movement problem in the bedroom, so the bed line and wall width matter first.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">02</span>
          <h3>Set the panel logic</h3>
          <p>Track quality, mirror ratio, and shutter alignment should be decided before the wardrobe turns into a loose visual concept.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card bw-wardrobe-route-card--accent">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">03</span>
          <h3>Move into estimate with a tighter brief</h3>
          <p>Once the format and internal access pattern feel right, the calculator and estimate flow can become genuinely useful.</p>
        </article>
      {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'hinged' %}
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">01</span>
          <h3>Check swing and access</h3>
          <p>Hinged wardrobes work best when door clearance and full-bay visibility are settled together instead of separately.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">02</span>
          <h3>Write the inside brief</h3>
          <p>Drawers, hanging, shelves, lofts, and lockable sections should be mapped as one storage system before pricing starts.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card bw-wardrobe-route-card--accent">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">03</span>
          <h3>Use the calculator or estimate next</h3>
          <p>When the room and internal structure are aligned, the wardrobe calculator and estimate button become the right next step.</p>
        </article>
      {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'walk-in' %}
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">01</span>
          <h3>Define the room zones</h3>
          <p>Walk-ins need circulation, dressing, storage, and mirror placement to be treated as one room plan.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">02</span>
          <h3>Balance openness and privacy</h3>
          <p>Open shelving, closed storage, and dressing surfaces should all be staged with intent, not left to the last minute.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card bw-wardrobe-route-card--accent">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">03</span>
          <h3>Consult once the zone map feels solid</h3>
          <p>Walk-ins become much easier to estimate when the room logic is in place and the customer is ready to discuss execution.</p>
        </article>
      {% else %}
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">01</span>
          <h3>Compare the three formats</h3>
          <p>Sliding, hinged, and walk-in each solve a different bedroom problem. This is where the customer should separate them cleanly.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">02</span>
          <h3>Write the storage list</h3>
          <p>Hanging, drawers, accessories, seasonal storage, and loft needs should be listed before the finish conversation starts.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-route-card bw-wardrobe-route-card--accent">
          <span class="bw-wardrobe-route-step">03</span>
          <h3>Use the calculator when the brief feels grounded</h3>
          <p>Once the customer has a format in mind, the wardrobe calculator and estimate flow move from browsing to planning.</p>
        </article>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-route-actions">
        <a class="bw-wardrobe-route-link" href="{{ calculator_cta_url }}">Open Wardrobe Calculator</a>
      <button class="bw-wardrobe-button--secondary" type="button" data-bw-wardrobe-estimate-open data-estimate-trigger="route">Get Free Estimate</button>
      <a class="bw-wardrobe-button--secondary" href="{{ contact_url }}">Talk To Bluewud</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bw-wardrobe-block bw-wardrobe-gallery">
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-head">
      <span class="bw-wardrobe-eyebrow">Wardrobe inspiration</span>
      {% if wardrobe_variant == 'sliding' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">See how sliding wardrobes can look in a calmer, room-led composition</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">The inspiration here should help the customer understand panel rhythm, mirror use, and the kind of room language sliding wardrobes create before they ask for pricing.</p>
      {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'hinged' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">See how hinged wardrobes can feel more premium with cleaner proportions</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">The gallery should make it easier to compare shutter depth, handle restraint, and the way a hinged elevation can sit in the bedroom without feeling heavy.</p>
      {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'walk-in' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">See how walk-in wardrobes become room-scale dressing environments</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">The gallery should help buyers imagine zoning, open display, mirrors, and storage balance instead of thinking only in cabinet terms.</p>
      {% else %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Use this gallery to narrow the wardrobe direction before the calculator</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">Images and product cues make the planning page easier to trust, especially when the buyer is still deciding whether sliding, hinged, or walk-in is the right fit.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-grid">
      <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-main">
        {% assign gallery_count = 0 %}
        {% if wardrobe_collection != blank %}
          {% for product in wardrobe_collection.products %}
            {% assign include_product = false %}
            {% assign product_title_downcase = product.title | downcase %}
            {% if wardrobe_variant == 'all' %}
              {% assign include_product = true %}
            {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'sliding' %}
              {% if product_title_downcase contains 'sliding' %}
                {% assign include_product = true %}
              {% endif %}
            {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'hinged' %}
              {% if product_title_downcase contains 'hinged' %}
                {% assign include_product = true %}
              {% endif %}
            {% elsif wardrobe_variant == 'walk-in' %}
              {% if product_title_downcase contains 'walk in' or product_title_downcase contains 'walk-in' %}
                {% assign include_product = true %}
              {% endif %}
            {% endif %}

            {% if include_product %}
              {% if gallery_count == 0 %}
                <article class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-main-card">
                  <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-main-copy">
                    <span class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-badge">Featured direction</span>
                    <h3>{{ product.title }}</h3>
                    <p>{{ product.description | strip_html | truncatewords: 28 }}</p>
                    <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-actions">
                      <a class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-link" href="{{ product.url }}">View Product</a>
        <a class="bw-wardrobe-button--secondary" href="{{ calculator_cta_url }}">Open Wardrobe Calculator</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-main-media">
                    {% if product.featured_image %}
                      {{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 1400 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', widths: '540, 720, 960, 1200, 1400', sizes: '(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 44vw', alt: product.title }}
                    {% endif %}
                  </div>
                </article>
              {% elsif gallery_count < 4 %}
                <article class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-card">
                  <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-media">
                    {% if product.featured_image %}
                      {{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 900 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', widths: '320, 460, 640, 900', sizes: '(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 18vw', alt: product.title }}
                    {% endif %}
                  </div>
                  <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-card-body">
                    <span class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-badge">{{ product.type | default: 'Wardrobe direction' }}</span>
                    <h3>{{ product.title }}</h3>
                    <p>{{ product.description | strip_html | truncatewords: 18 }}</p>
                    <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-actions">
                      <a class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-link" href="{{ product.url }}">Shortlist</a>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </article>
              {% endif %}
              {% assign gallery_count = gallery_count | plus: 1 %}
              {% if gallery_count >= 4 %}
                {% break %}
              {% endif %}
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        {% endif %}
      </div>

      <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-stack">
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-card">
          <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-media">
            {% if wardrobe_collection != blank and wardrobe_collection.products.first and wardrobe_collection.products.first.featured_image %}
              {{ wardrobe_collection.products.first.featured_image | image_url: width: 900 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', widths: '320, 460, 640, 900', sizes: '(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 18vw', alt: wardrobe_collection.products.first.title }}
            {% endif %}
          </div>
          <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-card-body">
            <span class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-badge">Planning cue</span>
            <h3>Keep the wardrobe picture room-led, not catalog-led</h3>
            <p>The strongest decisions start with clearance, access, and internal storage, then move to finish and detailing once the room feels grounded.</p>
            <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-actions">
          <a class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-link" href="{{ calculator_cta_url }}">Use Calculator</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-card">
          <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-media">
            {% if wardrobe_collection != blank and wardrobe_collection.products.size > 1 and wardrobe_collection.products[1].featured_image %}
              {{ wardrobe_collection.products[1].featured_image | image_url: width: 900 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', widths: '320, 460, 640, 900', sizes: '(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 18vw', alt: wardrobe_collection.products[1].title }}
            {% endif %}
          </div>
          <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-card-body">
            <span class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-badge">Detail cue</span>
            <h3>Let the finish support the room mood</h3>
            <p>Mirror use, wood tone, matte surfaces, and hardware restraint should all support the bedroom instead of dominating the wall.</p>
            <div class="bw-wardrobe-gallery-actions">
              <button class="bw-wardrobe-button--secondary" type="button" data-bw-wardrobe-estimate-open data-estimate-trigger="gallery">Get Free Estimate</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bw-wardrobe-block bw-wardrobe-journey">
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-head">
      <span class="bw-wardrobe-eyebrow">Planning path</span>
      {% if wardrobe_variant == 'all' %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Compare wardrobe types here, then move into the right pricing or estimate path</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">This page should not leave buyers trapped in inspiration mode. Use the wardrobe calculator for a wardrobe-led brief, compare kitchen scope when the modular package is expanding, step up to home interiors when the project crosses rooms, and open the estimate once the shortlist feels real.</p>
      {% else %}
        <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">Use this {{ spotlight_tag | downcase }} page as the wardrobe branch, then pick the next tool by project scope</h2>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">Once the likely wardrobe direction is visible, the next move should be clearer. Price the wardrobe itself, compare adjacent modular scope, shift to a whole-home calculator when more rooms are involved, or raise the estimate once the room brief is ready for Bluewud.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-journey-grid">
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-journey-card">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-journey-step">Step 1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Wardrobe Calculator</h3>
          <p>Use this when the project is wardrobe-first and this page already feels close to the right format, storage brief, and finish direction.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-journey-meta">Best when: you want a wardrobe-specific budget direction before talking.</p>
        <a class="bw-wardrobe-journey-link" href="{{ calculator_cta_url }}">Open Wardrobe Calculator</a>
      </article>
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-journey-card">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-journey-step">Step 2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Kitchen Calculator</h3>
          <p>Use this when the wardrobe is part of a broader modular package and the kitchen scope also needs to be priced in parallel before the call.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-journey-meta">Best when: wardrobe and kitchen decisions are being budgeted together.</p>
        <a class="bw-wardrobe-journey-link" href="{{ kitchen_calculator_url }}">Open Kitchen Calculator</a>
      </article>
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-journey-card">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-journey-step">Step 3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Home Interiors Calculator</h3>
          <p>Use this when the brief crosses rooms and the buyer needs one higher-level planning path instead of bouncing between isolated product pages.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-journey-meta">Best when: bedrooms, kitchen, and wider interiors are all in scope.</p>
        <a class="bw-wardrobe-journey-link" href="{{ interiors_calculator_url }}">Open Home Interiors Calculator</a>
      </article>
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-journey-card bw-wardrobe-journey-card--estimate">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-journey-step">Step 4</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Get Free Estimate</h3>
          <p>Use this once the room measurements, shortlist direction, and finish intent are clear enough to move from browsing into a real Bluewud conversation.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="bw-wardrobe-journey-meta">Best when: the project brief is ready for lead capture and callback.</p>
        <button class="bw-wardrobe-journey-link" type="button" data-bw-wardrobe-estimate-open data-estimate-trigger="journey">Get Free Estimate</button>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bw-wardrobe-block bw-wardrobe-consult">
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-head">
      <span class="bw-wardrobe-eyebrow">Consultation path</span>
      <h2 class="bw-wardrobe-title">How the wardrobe conversation should move once the customer is serious</h2>
      <p class="bw-wardrobe-copy">This is the part that turns browsing into a project brief: room context, shortlist, measurements, consultation, and then the estimate discussion.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bw-wardrobe-consult-grid">
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-consult-card">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-consult-step">01</span>
        <h3>Room snapshot</h3>
        <p>Capture the bedroom size, bed position, and front clearance so the format decision starts with reality.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-consult-card">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-consult-step">02</span>
        <h3>Shortlist and mood</h3>
        <p>Pick the likely wardrobe type, then decide whether the room needs a lighter, darker, or more feature-led composition.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-consult-card">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-consult-step">03</span>
        <h3>Measurement and internals</h3>
        <p>Map hanging, drawers, lofts, mirrors, and accessories before anyone asks for a final number.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="bw-wardrobe-consult-card bw-wardrobe-consult-card--accent">
        <span class="bw-wardrobe-consult-step">04</span>
        <h3>Estimate and callback</h3>
